            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Instagram supports three feed post sizes: square (1080x1080px, 1:1), portrait (1080x1350px, 4:5), and landscape (1080x566px, 1.91:1). Portrait 4:5 posts take up the most screen real estate and tend to get the best engagement. Max file size is 30MB for images."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What are the correct YouTube thumbnail dimensions?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "YouTube thumbnails should be 1280x720 pixels with a 16:9 aspect ratio. The minimum width is 640px and the max file size is 2MB. Use JPG, PNG, or GIF formats for best results."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What size should a TikTok video cover be?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "TikTok videos and covers use 1080x1920 pixels (9:16 aspect ratio). This is the standard vertical video format used across TikTok, Instagram Reels, and YouTube Shorts."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the recommended LinkedIn banner size?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "LinkedIn personal profile banners should be 1584x396 pixels (4:1 ratio). Company page cover images should be 1128x191 pixels. For shared link images, use 1200x627 pixels (1.91:1 ratio)."
          }
